All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
AddPartScreenController
This class contains control logic for the Add Part Screen, which is used to create In House and Outsourced parts.
AddProductScreenController
This class contains control logic for the Add Product Screen, which is used to create new products and add their associated parts.
InHouse
This class inherits from the Part class, and is used to create InHouse Part objects.
Inventory
This class is used to maintain Part and Product inventories.
main
This class contains methods that start the application.
MainScreenController
This class contains control logic for the Main Screen, which is used to add, modify, or delete parts and products in the inventory.
ModifyPartScreenController
This class contains control logic for the Modify Part Screen, which is used to modify the characteristics of existing Part objects.
ModifyProductScreenController
This class contains control logic for the Modify Product Screen, which is used to modify the characteristics of existing Product objects and add associated parts.
Outsourced
This class inherits from the Part class, and is used to create Outsourced Part objects.
Part
This abstract class serves as a model for InHouse and Outsourced classes to inherit from.
Product
This class is used to create Product objects.
